# RISOR — AI-Powered Second Brain

## Project Context
RISOR is a personal task and idea management system that captures unstructured brain dumps, classifies them using Claude AI, and organizes them using Eisenhower matrix prioritization, vector-based clustering, and goal-task hierarchies. Inspired by Karpathy's LLM Wiki pattern: raw data is compiled into persistent, compounding knowledge — not re-derived on every query.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 App Router (Server Components + Server Actions)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + pgvector + Auth + Edge Functions)
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components
- Claude API (Anthropic) for classification and reviews
- OpenAI API for embeddings (text-embedding-3-small, 1536d)

## Architecture Principles
- Server Components by default. Use 'use client' only when needed.
- Server Actions for all mutations.
- No client-side state management library.
- Supabase RLS for all data access.
- Classification self-improves via `classification_corrections` table.
- `user_synthesis` is a living document updated by every weekly review.
- `context_cache` is rebuilt nightly and injected into all LLM calls.
- Nightly `lint` checks catch orphaned goals, stale items, recurring patterns.
- Claude Haiku for classification, Sonnet for reviews/analysis.

## Database: Key Tables
- `items`: Core table. All brain dumps, tasks, ideas, goals. Has `embedding vector(1536)` + `search_vector tsvector`.
- `activity_log`: Every action logged for pattern detection.
- `classification_corrections`: Self-improving few-shot bank from user reclassifications.
- `user_synthesis`: Living compiled understanding, updated each review.
- `context_cache`: Pre-compiled context blobs for efficient LLM calls.
- `lint_results`: Nightly health check findings.
- `user_preferences`: Learned preferences that co-evolve with usage.

## Item Categories (8)
task, idea, project, research, learning, curiosity, art, reading

## Code Conventions
- `async function` not arrow for Server Actions
- Zod for all API validation
- kebab-case files, PascalCase components
- shadcn from '@/components/ui/'
- Never bypass RLS with service role key in client code
- Self-compassion in all user-facing language — never shame

## LLM Routing
- Haiku 4.5 (~70%): Classification, triage, dedup, auto-tagging
- Sonnet 4.6 (~20%): Weekly reviews, pattern analysis, affirmations
- Opus 4.6 (~10%): Quarterly strategic analysis (future)
